race.comment: SEAFALL (12) was poor at Flemington over this trip last time but was a leading market chance there having hit the line prior well at Caulfield Heath. She can bounce back. EXTREME VIRTUE (13) is another that struggled when well backed last time. She maps ideally down in the weights and can be in this for longer. SHINY NEW DEEL (5) faded late but not badly when last seen at Flemington, the win prior was good. 1800m suits now. MIDNITE STORM (7) made his Australian debut off 18 months and won well at Flemington. He likely gets a long way back around here but has to be considered.
